        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 4:56PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 455 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rensselaer Falls, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rensselaer Falls, Richville, Canton Village, Hermon Village, Clare,
Pierrepont, Hermon, De Kalb, Russell, Pitcairn, Edwards, Canton, De
Peyster, Fowler, Colton, Oswegatchie, Gouverneur, Parishville, Fine,
and Lisbon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
